        <h2>Network Management</h2>

        <p>Dr. Lavian offers network management expert consulting services. Network management refers to monitoring, maintaining, and optimizing a computer network to ensure reliable and efficient performance. It involves various activities, including monitoring network traffic, troubleshooting network issues, configuring network devices, and implementing security measures. Network management aims to ensure the network is available, secure, and performing optimally. It is typically carried out by a team of network administrators or IT professionals who are responsible for maintaining and managing the network. One standard framework for network management is the FCAPS model, which is an acronym for the following five areas:</p>

        <ul>
          <li>Fault.</li>
          <li>Configuration.</li>
          <li>Accounting.</li>
          <li>Performance.</li>
          <li>Security</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Network Management Technologies</h3>

        <p>Network management is the process of monitoring, maintaining, and optimizing computer networks. It uses various technologies and protocols, such as SNMP (Simple Network Management Protocol), to communicate with network devices and gather data. Network management systems (NMS) provide a centralized platform for network administrators to monitor and manage the network. NMS can be used to identify and resolve issues, optimize network performance, and ensure the security of the network.</p>

